{"questionId":"20910","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Particle A travels in a straight line such that its displacement, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi></math> metres, from a fixed origin&nbsp;after <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds is given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>10</mn></math>, as shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/02915798495d49d6a9e8f1a26608c8f79648d79a.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Particle A starts at the origin and passes through the origin again when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>setting&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp; (accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> if the candidate’s final answer includes additional solutions&nbsp;(such as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mn>8</mn></math>).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20910","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.9a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of p.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.9—Kinematics problems"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}